# The only committed fixture is fixtures/transcript_vector.json (a frozen Keccak
# transcript known-answer vector). Every other fixture -- keys, proofs, digests,
# and the meta.json metadata -- is git-ignored and regenerable on demand, because
# the keys are large and the proofs are randomized. Regenerate with:
#   Rust exports (proof.bin, vk.bin, vk_digest.bin, meta.json, and cubic/ copies):
#     cargo test --lib export_reference_fixtures -- --ignored --nocapture
#     cargo test --lib export_cubic_fixtures     -- --ignored --nocapture
#   Reference-prover proof against the Rust vk (cubic/python_proof.bin):
#     python3 reference/tests/test_prove_finish.py
#   Fully stand-alone Python setup + proof (cubic/python_vk.bin,
#   cubic/python_standalone_proof.bin):
#     python3 reference/tests/test_standalone.py
fixtures/*.bin
fixtures/*/*.bin
fixtures/meta.json
fixtures/cubic/meta.json

# Python bytecode
__pycache__/
*.pyc
